RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 120000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEORGE'S HONEY prompted the pace two wide and between horses, forged an advantage at the furlong pole and drove clear. UNMATCHED tracked in the three to four path around the turn, lacked progress while hanging on her left lead through midstretch, yet ran on late as ahead foes tired and gained place in the final sixteenth. DEBOISBLANC broke slowly, gained outside of rivals to press three wide entering the turn, bid turning for home, but was turned away in upper stretch, kept on to re-bid for place in the final sixteenth, but was outkicked by an outer rival soon after. SAPPHIRE NIGHTS broke inwardly towards open space, set the pace as a pair of outer rivals applied stern pressure, clung to a margin through upper stretch, but was headed at the furlong pole and weakened in the final sixteenth. HONOR CAT tracked along the inside while a bit off of the rail, chased behind the leaders through upper stretch, then stayed on three wide late, but failed to threaten. AIM HIGHER broke a step slow, lacked speed in the four path, and failed to factor on her left lead. GREEN CHILE broke slowly and was outrun in the five path.

SUNDAY SHOES tracked four wide, ranged up to the leader under rousing around the turn, but quickly proved no match for that one in upper stretch, and fended off an inner place-bidding foe through the final sixteenth. PROMISE OF HOPE trailed along the inside, vacated the rail to surpass a tiring rival turning for home, tipped back to the fence in upper stretch, then rallied along it to bid for place in the final sixteenth, but was denied reaching that position. B G WARRIOR chased in the three path and between horses, but gave way. HOLIDAY DECISION chased outside of the leader while inside of other rivals into the turn, but weakened at the three furlong pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: V V'S DREAM broke slowly, raced off of the pace two wide into the turn, launched a rally by splitting foes in the four path turning for home, then rallied in the five path under confident handling to sweep past the leader at the sixteenth pole before kicking clear. CHEETAH MISS quickly sped clear, opened up a wide margin into the turn, showed the way in the two path around the bend, held sway from pursuing foes into midstretch, but was overhauled by the eventual winner approaching the final sixteenth, and held place safely. HI'IAKA laid off of the pace along the inside, shifted out to the three path in midstretch, and rallied to reach show at the wire. GLORIETTE tracked two wide, ranged up turning for home before shifting to the four path entering the lane, but only managed to chase the clear leader through upper stretch, got outkicked for place at the furlong grounds, then was nailed at the wire for show. ARGAN raced off of the pace in the four to five path around the turn, then failed to menace between horses. VIBE CHECK broke slowly, trailed in the two path, fanned to the six path in upper stretch, and failed to threaten outside of rivals. TX WOMEN FOR ARTS stalked along the inside, but only managed to chase in upper stretch before fading. LITTLE MUSIC chased two wide but weakened between horses at the three furlong pole.

Non-winners Of $24,600 On The Turf Since March 19 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where E ntered For $35,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five and a Half Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGH FRONT stalked along the inside, bid and struck the front passing the five sixteenths pole, kicked clear in upper stretch, and desperately lasted from a pair of late bidders at the wire. B D VALESKI pursued from midpack two wide, awaited racing room entering the lane, split foes in upper stretch, rallied along with an outer rival to offer a bid approaching the wire, but narrowly came up short. COUNTERSTRIKE tracked four wide, spun into the lane five wide, grinded away while shifting inwardly on his lead in midstretch, straightened and sustained his charge to bid in the closing stages, but missed. ARABIAN PRINCE laid off of the pace in the three path and between horses, tipped to the five path in midstretch and offered a late rally to gain fourth in the shadow of the wire. GILDED RULER was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, tracked along the inside, vied for place with outer foes nearing midstretch, but yielded through the final sixteenth. LAVER lacked speed in the two path, shifted out to the six path in upper stretch, and ran on. TRUST DADDY stalked three wide, spun into the lane four wide, but was outkicked while put to tight quarters among foes at the furlong grounds and weakened. GROUP EIGHTEEN took contact from an inner rival before steadying from pinched quarters at the start, lacked speed four to five path, and drifted in through the lane while failing to factor. BRAZEN BOY broke a beat slow, laid off of the pace in the four path, fanned to the eight path in upper stretch and made little impact. KING OF SONG broke outwardly and bothered multiple rivals at the start, set the pace in the two path, but was headed by a rail bidder at the five sixteenths pole, then caved three wide and between horses at the three sixteenths marker. ROMAN GIANT was outrun along the inside. FINGERS transferred contact from an inner rival to an outer foe while being forced outwardly at the start, pursued from midpack along the inside into the turn and weakened around the bend.
